Ahead of the crucial Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) polls, the State Election Commission has directed the chief secretary, GNTCD and all the three municipal commissioners to take action with regards to the removal of the words 'Aam Aadmi from all forms of display. Party chief Arvind Kejriwal has made elaborate plans and will be addressing a series of meetings across Delhi. A Delhi Bharatiya Janata Party delegation on Monday had met State Election Commissioner and made efforts towards the removal of words 'Aam Aadmi' from government-run schemes.The delegation led by Gupta said that AAP should not be allowed to use its official position while campaigning. 